### CSS Lists

Style ordered (`<ol>`) and unordered (`<ul>`) lists.

---

### List Style Type

```css
/* Unordered list markers */
list-style-type: disc;     /* Default filled circle */
list-style-type: circle;   /* Empty circle */
list-style-type: square;   /* Square */
list-style-type: none;     /* No marker */

/* Ordered list markers */
list-style-type: decimal;           /* 1, 2, 3... */
list-style-type: decimal-leading-zero; /* 01, 02... */
list-style-type: lower-roman;       /* i, ii, iii... */
list-style-type: upper-roman;       /* I, II, III... */
list-style-type: lower-alpha;       /* a, b, c... */
list-style-type: upper-alpha;       /* A, B, C... */

/* Emoji markers */
list-style-type: "\2713"; /* Custom string marker */
```

---

### List Style Position

```css
list-style-position: outside; /* Marker outside the content (default) */
list-style-position: inside;  /* Marker inside with content */
```

---

### List Style Image

```css
ul {
  list-style-image: url('bullet.png');
}
```

---

### Shorthand

```css
/* type position image */
list-style: square inside;
list-style: none;            /* Remove all markers */
list-style: url('bullet.png') circle inside;
```

---

### Removing Default Styles

```css
nav ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
  margin: 0;
}
```

---

### Custom Bullet Colors

CSS doesn't have direct bullet color. Use `::before` instead:

```css
.custom-list {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
}

.custom-list li::before {
  content: "\2022";   /* Bullet character */
  color: red;
  font-weight: bold;
  display: inline-block;
  width: 1em;
  margin-left: -1em;
}
```

---

### Horizontal Navigation (Display: Inline)

```css
nav ul {
  list-style: none;
  padding: 0;
}

nav li {
  display: inline-block;
  margin-right: 20px;
}
```

---

> **Best Practice:** Always set `list-style: none` with `padding: 0` for navigation menus.
